---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <nav class="topbar">
    <a href="#top" class="wordmark">NoVibe</a>
    <div class="navlinks">
      <a href="#act-1">I</a>
      <a href="#act-2">II</a>
      <a href="#landing">Climb</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main id="top">
    <header class="hero">
      <p class="kicker reveal">The NoVibe Manifesto</p>
      <h1 class="headline reveal">Coding was never the&nbsp;work.</h1>
      <p class="deck reveal">
        So making it free did not make software free. They call it
        <em>vibe coding</em> &mdash; describe it, ship it, done. It is a
        comforting lie about where the work actually lives.
      </p>
      <dl class="proof reveal">
        <div>
          <dt>11%</dt>
          <dd>of a developer&rsquo;s day is actually spent writing code</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>19% slower</dt>
          <dd>experienced devs <em>with</em> AI &mdash; while sure they were faster</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>50&ndash;200&times;</dt>
          <dd>the cost to fix what you got wrong in the requirements</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </header>

    <section id="act-1" class="act">
      <p class="act-num reveal">I</p>
      <h2 class="act-title reveal">Most of the work was always invisible</h2>

      <article class="spine reveal">
        <h3>Coding is the last mile, not the journey.</h3>
        <p>
          Writing code is the smallest, last part of building software &mdash;
          and AI made exactly that part cheap. The work that remains is the work
          that was always hard: deciding what to build, designing it, proving it
          right, and keeping it alive.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="spine reveal">
        <h3>Intent is the work, not output.</h3>
        <p>
          A few words of hope become a mountain of code that cannot be what you
          meant &mdash; because you never said what you meant. The gaps you
          leave are filled by the machine&rsquo;s defaults, not your intent.
          Specify the essential; do not drown in the generated.
        </p>
      </article>

      <p class="aside reveal">
        And when you skip that work, you do not get magic &mdash; you get
        danger. Insecure, ill&#8209;formed code ships easily now, because the
        risk lived in the requirements you never set.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="act-2" class="act">
      <p class="act-num reveal">II</p>
      <h2 class="act-title reveal">What changed, and what no one is building for</h2>

      <article class="spine reveal">
        <h3>Change got cheap, so quality is a choice.</h3>
        <p>
          For decades, quality was a budget &mdash; refactoring, structure, and
          documentation were the first things cut when time ran short. That has
          inverted. A clean, coherent system is no longer a luxury you fight
          for. It is a default you choose.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="spine reveal">
        <h3>There is a tool gap, and no one is naming it.</h3>
        <p>
          The talk is all of models and prompts; the tools go unmentioned. They
          were built for one person typing &mdash; but the work has moved to
          deciding, designing, verifying, and coordinating, together. Between
          what the work now asks and what the tools offer lies a gap no one is
          closing.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="landing" class="landing">
      <p class="landing-intro reveal">
        The machine writes the code now. That leaves two ways to work.
      </p>

      <div class="dichotomy reveal">
        <div class="col passenger">
          <p class="role">
            <span class="role-kind">Passenger</span>the translator
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>turns requirements into code</li>
            <li>audits what the machine made</li>
            <li>trapped in review hell</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>

        <div class="col driver">
          <p class="role">
            <span class="role-kind">Driver</span>the author
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>shapes the work</li>
            <li>owns it &mdash; intent to ship</li>
            <li>design &middot; judgment &middot; taste</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="reveal punch">Be the driver, never the passenger.</p>
    </section>

    <footer class="foot">
      <span>NoVibe</span>
      <a href="https://github.com/novibe-org" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
        >novibe&#8209;org</a
      >
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .topbar {
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0 0 auto 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 1.1rem clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--bg) 82%, transparent);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    z-index: 10;
    transition: border-color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .topbar.scrolled {
    border-bottom-color: var(--line);
  }

  .wordmark {
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .navlinks {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.4rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .navlinks a {
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .navlinks a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  main {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: clamp(1.25rem, 6vw, 2rem);
  }

  .hero {
    padding-block: clamp(6.5rem, 13vh, 8.5rem) clamp(3rem, 6vh, 4.5rem);
  }

  .kicker {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }

  .headline {
    font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 7vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 1.04;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    text-wrap: balance;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .deck {
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.4vw, 1.4rem);
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 34rem;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .deck em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
    border-bottom: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 45%, transparent);
  }

  .proof {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    margin-top: clamp(2.5rem, 6vh, 4rem);
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .proof dt {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.4vw, 2.1rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--accent);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .proof dd {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .proof em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 38rem) {
    .proof {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.4rem;
    }
  }

  .act {
    padding-block: var(--space);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .act-num {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--faint);
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }

  .act-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 3.4vw, 1.85rem);
    line-height: 1.22;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    margin-bottom: 3.2rem;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .spine {
    margin-bottom: 2.8rem;
  }

  .spine h3 {
    font-size: 1.18rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
  }

  .spine p {
    color: #34343c;
  }

  .aside {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .landing {
    padding-block: var(--space);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .landing-intro {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: clamp(2.25rem, 5vh, 3rem);
    max-width: 28rem;
  }

  .dichotomy {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 6vh, 3.5rem);
  }

  .divider {
    width: 1px;
    align-self: stretch;
    background: var(--line);
  }

  .col .role {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .role-kind {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .col ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }

  .col li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* passenger = faded, the role you refuse */
  .passenger {
    color: var(--faint);
  }
  .passenger .role-kind {
    color: var(--faint);
  }

  /* driver = vivid, the role you take */
  .driver .role {
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .driver .role-kind {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .driver li {
    color: #34343c;
  }

  .punch {
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 4.8vw, 2.6rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  @media (max-width: 34rem) {
    .dichotomy {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.75rem;
    }
    .divider {
      width: auto;
      height: 1px;
    }
  }

  .foot {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding-block: 2.5rem 3.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--faint);
  }

  .foot a {
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .foot a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* scroll reveal */
  .reveal {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(14px);
    transition:
      opacity 0.7s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),
      transform 0.7s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
  }

  .reveal.in {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: none;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .reveal {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: none;
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Stagger-reveal sections as they scroll into view.
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      for (const e of entries) {
        if (e.isIntersecting) {
          e.target.classList.add("in");
          io.unobserve(e.target);
        }
      }
    },
    { threshold: 0.12, rootMargin: "0px 0px -8% 0px" },
  );
  document.querySelectorAll(".reveal").forEach((el) => io.observe(el));

  // Hairline under the topbar once the hero is scrolled past.
  const bar = document.querySelector(".topbar");
  const onScroll = () => bar?.classList.toggle("scrolled", window.scrollY > 40);
  onScroll();
  window.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll, { passive: true });
</script>
